      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-19T15:52:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Landed changes as suggested here.",
      "parentUuid": "ea8448a2_c82c0a43",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 574,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 574,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "684bbbfcca0db40d294b4d9bf50936d8749e9b81",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c98478bc_fd31e2e4",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrDrawingManager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 941,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-12T13:23:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "during flushIfNecessary do we want to do a submit? For GL I feel like the answer would be no, but for other backends I think we need to so we can try and free up resources as soon as possible even if it is not immediately this frame. Though if we don\u0027t submit I believe most of the newer APIs don\u0027t hold refs to GrGpuResources in their command buffers, but to the gpu objects themselves. So technically all we need is the flush to clear up our tracking of GrGpuResources even though the actual objects are still alive.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 941,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 941,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "684bbbfcca0db40d294b4d9bf50936d8749e9b81",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0d8e5a17_68a2345c",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrDrawingManager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 941,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-12T19:42:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Personally, I think we should be moving towards removing flushIfNecessary(). I think most of our clients want explicit control over when things like this happen. Many of our allocations have been moved to flush time anyway and most clients explicitly make texture-backed images rather than using the SW image cache.",
      "parentUuid": "c98478bc_fd31e2e4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 941,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 941,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "684bbbfcca0db40d294b4d9bf50936d8749e9b81",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16e9ec12_86597345",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrDrawingManager.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 941,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-19T15:52:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah I know that\u0027s our longer term goal. For now I think I\u0027ll leave the submit here to keep things work as they do today. Hopefully we can just remove the whole function sooner rather than later.",
      "parentUuid": "0d8e5a17_68a2345c",
